CODE BLOCKS

1.Remove unwanted samples
- Inputs: Video(avi), Label file(txt), Sensor limits
- Outputs: corrected video(avi), corrected label(txt)
- Description: It should remove all the samples with no sensor reading, first 10 frames of the video(initalization lag), sensor readings are out of the given limits


2.Convert to grayscale
- Inputs:Color video(avi)
- Outputs: Grayscale video(avi)

3.Image processing algorithms
- Inputs: Raw grayscale video(avi), Algorithm parameters
- Outputs: Processed video(avi)

4.Convert video to text
- Inputs: Video(avi)
- Outputs: Features(txt)

5.Predict
- Inputs:Test data(txt),NNET file(xml), NNET layersize(numpy)
- Outputs:Time per prediction, Total time taken, Predicted labels(txt)

6.Train
- Inputs: Training data(txt),Training labels(txt),NNET layersize(numpy), BACKPROP parameters(txt/numpy)
- Outputs: No. of iterations, Time taken for training, NNET file(xml)

7.Perfomance Measure
- Inputs: NNET file(xml),Data file(txt), Label file(txt)
- Outputs: All the performance measure for that prediction

8.Manual labelling of data
- Inputs: Test data(avi), Individual labels
- Outputs: Labels(txt)
